Nigerian singer, Peter Okoye, popularly known as Mr P, has reacted to the statement of the 2023 presidential aspirant, Dele Momodu in regards to Peter Obi’s choice of party. Recall that Momodu during an interview with TVC, Your View, stated that Obi cannot win the presidential election on the platform of Labour Party, claiming that the party doesn’t have a structure. “You cannot win the presidential election from a fringe, local party. Peter Obi has money but can Peter Obi spend his hard-earned money on fighting an Atiku?” -Advertisement- Reacting to this, the musician via his official Twitter page on Tuesday stated that Obi might not have the money and structure but he has won the hearts of the youths, masses, and the people He wrote, “With all due Respect Sir Mr. Dele Momodu! Yes, Peter Obi might not have the money and structure! “But he has the Youths, the Masses, and The People now!. The truth is that we the people are the structure. “We are many and we are powerful. We are Obi-deint, we can not be distracted.” With all due Respect Sir Mr Dele Momodu! Yes Peter Obi might not have the money and structure! But he has the Youths,The Masses and The People now!. The truth is that we the people are the structure. We are many and we are powerful. We are Obi-deint we can not be distracted.